# Release Notes Rules

- Production release notes live in `docs/release-notes/`.
- When preparing a repository GitHub Release, write the release note section as the final publish-ready body. Do not label it as a draft, suggested draft, or temporary copy.
- Use the heading `## GitHub Release Body` for the text that should be pasted into the GitHub Release description.
- Keep the body self-contained: summarize user-visible changes, important fixes, artifact names, checksums when useful, and operational notes needed by users of the packaged build.
- Avoid including process-only wording such as "draft", "suggested", "copy later", or "to be edited before publishing" unless the user explicitly asks for an internal planning note.
